metadata.name: Streetline #001
metadata.description:
Concrete, metal, and plastic shape the world through lines, curves, and angles, which become an integral part of our lives. In a symbiotic relationship, we depend on these structures more and more, at the same time as they take us away from our natural environment.  
--  
Tokenized image from the 'Streetlines' collection by photographers Oliver Reinis and Shirley Reinis.

This is an ERC-721  1/1 edition minted on a manifold smart contract.

It serves as a VIP Pass for future airdrops and other exclusive content.

More information and the history of the collection here:  
https://reiniscouple.space

1695 x 2119 px  
300dpi  
2022
